TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Value Issue of Business: The Responsibility of the Businessman
AU  - Elbing, Alvar O.
Y1  - 1970/03/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254927
DO  - 10.5465/254927
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 79
EP  - 89
VL  - 13
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In the arena of today's social value problems, the businessman is accused and victimized by his own professional rationale?a rationale derived from traditional economic theory. This rationale, unlike that of other professions (e.g., law or medicine), does not consist of an ideal value standard, but rather is an abstract caricature of self-interest. This rationale must be abandoned for a social (rather than a purely economic) model, one which realistically clarifies the nature of the social co-responsibility inherent in the businessman' s professional role.
AB  - In the arena of today's social value problems, the businessman is accused and victimized by his own professional rationale?a rationale derived from traditional economic theory. This rationale, unlike that of other professions (e.g., law or medicine), does not consist of an ideal value standard, but rather is an abstract caricature of self-interest. This rationale must be abandoned for a social (rather than a purely economic) model, one which realistically clarifies the nature of the social co-responsibility inherent in the businessman' s professional role.
