TY  - JOUR
T1  - Leadership and Motivation: A Core Concept
AU  - Evans, Martin G.
Y1  - 1970/03/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254928
DO  - 10.5465/254928
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 91
EP  - 102
VL  - 13
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - An attempt is made here to deepen the understanding of Supervisor/Subordinate relationships by examining the impact of a supervisor's behavior upon the motivational state of his subordinates. This is done by outlining a path-goal theory of human motivation and by examining the major articulations between variables in this theory and variables of supervisory behavior (Initiation of structure and Consideration). The results of a survey that was carried out to test these inter-relationships are briefly reported and some implications for organizational development through supervisory training are suggested.
AB  - An attempt is made here to deepen the understanding of Supervisor/Subordinate relationships by examining the impact of a supervisor's behavior upon the motivational state of his subordinates. This is done by outlining a path-goal theory of human motivation and by examining the major articulations between variables in this theory and variables of supervisory behavior (Initiation of structure and Consideration). The results of a survey that was carried out to test these inter-relationships are briefly reported and some implications for organizational development through supervisory training are suggested.
